# ~/.claude dotfiles — curated, portable config only.
# Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING by default, then explicitly track the handful of
# files/dirs that are safe and useful to carry across devices. This keeps
# credentials, caches, and private session transcripts out of git by default.

/*

# --- tracked config ---
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/settings.json
!/CLAUDE.md
!/keybindings.json
!/skills/
# agent-development: proprietary (anthropics/claude-code, All-rights-reserved) —
# local-only, must NOT go in the public repo
/skills/agent-development/
!/commands/
!/agents/
!/hooks/

# --- word of the day (lock screen): updated daily by the 7am cloud routine,
#     fetched by ~/.local/bin/word-of-the-day-fetch on this laptop ---
!/word-of-the-day.json

# --- plugin config (NOT the cached clones, installed plugins, or the
#     auto-generated known_marketplaces.json which embeds an absolute path) ---
!/plugins/
/plugins/*
!/plugins/config.json

# Note: settings.local.json is intentionally NOT tracked — it holds
# machine-specific permission rules (paths to external drives, etc.).
